{"id":14881235,"mediaExerciseId":"96145e26-666e-4d1c-a40a-156c8e539e46","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"10","chapterTitle":"Making Capital Investment Decisions","groupId":612342,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":342,"solutions":[{"id":6280890,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will solve for the cash flow amount that will be used as an initial investment for the project. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"By definition, the initial investment refers to the amount of cash that is needed to cover the costs of setting up a new project. This is important to assess to reduce the risk of the project failing at the early stage due to lack of funding. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"In order to solve for this, we must first categorized the values given in the problem.\n\nTo start, the amount in which they bought the company before is considered as a sunk cost since it will no longer have any effect on the current cash flow. \n\nThe other values presented in the problem will then be the ones considered for the initial investment.  ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"To solve for the initial investment, we will simply add all the values except the sunk cost. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Initial Investment}&=\\$4,100,000+\\$18,100,000+\\$950,000\\\\\n&=\\$23,150,000\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe initial investment needed in the project is $\\$23,150,000$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"6b540398-901c-4f1d-b90b-9a8877d8647d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881236,"exerciseName":"2","page":342,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fb29d0a8-b182-4810-9962-e160980db5f3","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-questions-and-problems-2-fb29d0a8-b182-4810-9962-e160980db5f3"},{"id":14881238,"exerciseName":"4","page":342,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6f9243ac-f8ce-4bd3-b483-11c9777a6aa0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-questions-and-problems-4-6f9243ac-f8ce-4bd3-b483-11c9777a6aa0"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881234,"exerciseName":"10","page":342,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"da09c3d5-01f5-4c86-9907-aa65d4bb0bf9","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-questions-and-problems-10-da09c3d5-01f5-4c86-9907-aa65d4bb0bf9"},{"id":14881233,"exerciseName":"9","page":342,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"41bfc574-7cd1-499d-a0b9-d5f3c1757ac1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-questio